-- NWR to Invest Over 500 Million Euros Into Debiensko, WSJ Reports
-- B y   L a d k a   B a u e r o v a
-- 2012-03-05T13:15:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-05/nwr-to-invest-over-500-million-euros-into-debiensko-wsj-reports.html
New World Resources Plc, the largest
Czech coking-coal producer, is investing more than 500 million
euros ($661 million) into its Debiensko mine in  Poland ,  Wall
Street Journal  reported, citing an interview with billionaire
Zdenek Bakala.  The development of the Debiensko project will take about
five years, the newspaper said, citing Bakala, whose investment
firm BXR Group owns a 64 percent stake in NWR.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Ladka Bauerova in Prague at 
 lbauerova@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
